Here is my code : 

public static void generationPDF(
		File fileXML,
		File fileXSL,
		File filePDF)
		throws IOException, SAXException, FOPException
	{
		Logger log = new ConsoleLogger(ConsoleLogger.LEVEL_WARN);
		MessageHandler.setScreenLogger(log);

		XSLTInputHandler input = new XSLTInputHandler(fileXML, fileXSL);

		Driver driver = new Driver();
		driver.setLogger(log);

		driver.setRenderer(Driver.RENDER_PDF);
		driver.setOutputStream(
			new BufferedOutputStream(new FileOutputStream
(filePDF)));
		driver.render(input.getParser(), input.getInputSource());
	}

When using the BufferedOutputStream, the PDF file is corrupted.
Without BufferedOutputStream (just FileOutputStream) all is OK.

There are few diffrences between the two files but Acrobat Reader can't read 
the first.
